sp.p:
I have here two Mistresses, but if the best were chosen out, 
if Poliphemus to there ye were out, his choice might be as good as Argus broad waking, 
so difficult is the difference.

Aye, you shall answer it in the Senate house, the Emperor shall know it: 
if she be my child, I will rule her, I will bridle her: 
I will curb her: I will rain her, 
if she will not, let her go, starve, beg, hang, draw, sink, swim she gets not a doit, 
a denier, I will not own her.
